===Etymology===
From the belief that the metal [[silver]] can harm [[supernatural]] creatures, e.g. [[werewolf|werewolves]].  In movies, silver bullets are frequently an expedient end to a monster problem.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[silver]] [[bullet]]}}
# {{idiom}} Metaphorically, any [[straightforward]] [[solution]] perceived to have extreme [[effectiveness]] or [[miraculous]] results.
#:''There is no '''silver bullet''' for this problem.  It will take hard work and long hours to fix.''

